I was walking through the area and noticed this place so I went in and ordered the ceviche de camarónes and a  encebollado de pescado (fish soup). The soup was salty and the camarones were of those precooked frozen. I called the place and a lady answered and when I asked about the shrimp she stood quiet and then after a few second she said she get from a guy that’s sells to them. I ate a few spoons and my stomach is upset. :(  I will not be buying from this place again. $24 lost!
